<h3>When Traditional Automation Still Works</h3>
<p>Not every workflow needs AI. Simple transactional emails (order confirmations, password resets) work fine with basic automation. <a href="/blog/email-automation-guide/">Email automation</a> for standard drip sequences does not always require machine learning.</p>
<p>The crossover point comes when you need personalization at scale, optimization across dozens of variables, or predictive capabilities. That is where AI automation earns its cost.</p>
